(Issue Number:  17-018)312 1881 MS
(Title:         Clarification of C function-like macros)312 1921 MS
(Section:       17.3.1.2 [)312 1961 MS
(lib.headers])887 1961 MS
(Status:        Open)312 2001 MS
(Description:)312 2081 MS
(The current WP\222s description of C headers is unclear as to the treatment of)312 2161 MS
(macros.  The current wording of 17.3.1.2 paragraph 4 is:)312 2201 MS
(Except as noted in Clauses 18 through 27, the contents of each header)462 2281 MS
(cname shall be the same as that of the corresponding header )462 2321 MS
(name.h, as)1842 2321 MS
(specified in ISO C \(Clause  7\), or Amendment 1, \(Clause 7\), as)462 2361 MS
(appropriate.  In this C++ Standard library, however, the declarations)462 2401 MS
(and definitions are within namespace scope _)462 2441 MS
(basic.scope.namespace_ of)1474 2441 MS
(the namespace std.)462 2481 MS
(Resolution:)312 2561 MS
(   Replace 17.3.1.2 paragraph 4 of the Working Paper with:)312 2641 MS
(Except as noted in Clauses 18 through 27, the contents of each header)462 2721 MS
(cname shall be the same as that of the corresponding header )462 2761 MS
(name.h, as)1842 2761 MS
(specified in )462 2801 MS
(ISO/IEC 9899:1990 Programming Languages C )761 2801 MS
(\(Clause 7\) , or)1727 2801 MS
(ISO/IEC:1990 Programming Languages \226 C AMENDMENT 1: C Integrity)462 2841 MS
(,)1911 2841 MS
(\(Clause 4\), as appropriate, as if by inclusion. In the C++ Standard)462 2881 MS
(library, however, the declarations and definitions \(except for names)462 2921 MS
