(Work Group:    Library Clause 17)312 1321 MS
(Issue Number:  17-019)312 1361 MS
(Title:         C++ headers with .h forms)312 1401 MS
(Section:       \(Annex D\) D.4 [)312 1441 MS
(depr.c.headers])1002 1441 MS
(Status:        Open)312 1481 MS
(Description:)312 1561 MS
([from lib-4548])312 1641 MS
(I have been looking at issue 17-007 of the Clause 17 Issues list which was)312 1721 MS
(accepted into the WP at the Santa Cruz meeting. This issue added )312 1761 MS
(fstream.h,)1807 1761 MS
(iomanip.h, )312 1801 MS
(iostream.h and )565 1801 MS
(new.h to the list of C++ .h headers  provided by the)910 1801 MS
(library  so that existing programs will continue to work and do approximately)312 1841 MS
(the same things. The intent is for each of the above mentioned headers to)312 1881 MS
(include the corresponding C++ Standard version of the header followed by the)312 1921 MS
(using declaration for each symbol in the header.)312 1961 MS
(This will not really provide a compatible solution. Unlike the .h versions of)312 2041 MS
(the C  headers provided for compatibility the  above mentioned headers have)312 2081 MS
(not been previously defined in a standard way. This means that  the content of)312 2121 MS
(each of these headers will vary at least subtly in each existing)312 2161 MS
(implementation. Since the contents of the .h headers are non-Standard it is)312 2201 MS
(also difficult to determine how different their contents are from the existing)312 2241 MS
(C++ versions of the headers. For example  <)312 2281 MS
(fstream>, <)1301 2281 MS
(iomanip> and <)1554 2281 MS
(iostream>)1876 2281 MS
(are now )312 2321 MS
(templatized.  In <new> the default declaration of new\(\) throws an)496 2321 MS
(exception whereas the declaration in most existing versions of )312 2361 MS
(new.h would)1761 2361 MS
(not.)312 2401 MS
(It seems likely that providing C++ Standard versions of )312 2481 MS
(fstream.h, )1600 2481 MS
(iomanip.h,)1853 2481 MS
(iostream.h and )312 2521 MS
(new.h  opens the  door  to lots  of compatibility problems. The)657 2521 MS
(includer of the .h headers may reasonably expect their "old" implementation)312 2561 MS
(defined behavior not the  C++ Standard one. It will also make it more)312 2601 MS
(difficult for library vendors to provide a completely backward compatible)312 2641 MS
(header file solution.)312 2681 MS
(Resolution:)312 2761 MS
(D.4 paragraph 4 currently reads:)312 2841 MS
(The C++ headers)462 2921 MS
