(<---------------------------------------------------------------------->)312 1193 MS
(Work Group:    Library Clause 17)312 1273 MS
(Issue Number:  17-020)312 1313 MS
(Title:         Clarification of exceptions thrown by library)312 1353 MS
(Section:       17.3.4.8 [)312 1393 MS
(lib.res.on.exception.handling])887 1393 MS
(Status:        Open)312 1433 MS
(Description:)312 1513 MS
(   In private email, Jonathan )312 1593 MS
(Schilling wrote:)1002 1593 MS
(>I looked at the complex class, which is completely silent)462 1673 MS
(>on error handling \(other than for the I/O operators\).  Does this mean)462 1713 MS
(>that)462 1753 MS
(>)462 1793 MS
(>       there are no error conditions, or)462 1833 MS
(>)462 1873 MS
(>       error conditions result in undefined behavior, or)462 1913 MS
(>)462 1953 MS
(>       errors are reported using the C math library method, or)462 1993 MS
(>)462 2033 MS
(>       errors will result in \(predefined?\) exceptions being thrown)462 2073 MS
(   Beman Dawes comments:)312 2153 MS
(I think we want to give considerable flexibility to implementors. We)462 2233 MS
(would, however, like to encourage the reporting of errors by throwing)462 2273 MS
(exceptions, and encourage that those exceptions are from \(or derived)462 2313 MS
(from\) the standard exception classes.)462 2353 MS
(Resolution:)312 2433 MS
(   Change the Working Paper 17.3.4.8 [)312 2513 MS
(lib.res.on.exception.handling] from:)1186 2513 MS
(Any of the functions defined in the C++ Standard library that do not)462 2593 MS
(have an exception-specification may throw any exception. An)462 2633 MS
(implementation may strengthen this implicit exception-specification by)462 2673 MS
(adding an explicit one.)462 2713 MS
(   To:)312 2793 MS
(Any of the functions defined in the C++ Standard library that do not)462 2873 MS
(have an exception-specification may throw implementation-defined)462 2913 MS
